Flask app for AI image generation and approvals
================================================

Overview
--------
This app replaces the CSV approval loop by storing generated variants in Redshift (`temp.image_to_approve`) and exposing a simple UI for reviewers to approve/reject. Once approved, the app triggers the existing Oracle/S3 workflow.

Main features
-------------
- Run generation jobs based on Redshift queries and file-based prompts
- Store variants + prompts + metadata in `temp.image_to_approve`
- Review UI: list/paginate, preview original vs variant, approve/reject, add notes
- Background job to process approvals via your `process_approved_variants.py` flow

Setup
-----
1. Create and fill your `.env` with keys: REDSHIFT_*, AWS_*, ORACLE_*, OPEN_AI_API_KEY, API_SECRET, FLASK_SECRET_KEY
2. pip install -r requirements.txt
3. flask --app flask_app.app run (or `python -m flask_app.app`)

